    "created_at": "2015-08-25T04:07:55Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-08-25T04:07:55Z",
    "body": "The normal APIs on each platform to register global hotkeys do not allow overriding other application's registered hotkeys (especially those used by the operating system), this is to reduce surprises to users and give your system peace (imaging apps scrambling for hotkeys).\n\nOf course there are many ways to rob the hotkeys from other apps and even the operating system, but it makes us look like virus, and is bad anyway, so we are not going to do that.\n"
  },
